Tauraruwar White Lines Laura Haddock, mai shekara 34, ta je neman gida tare da masoyinta mai shekaru 28 Tom Rhys Harries
Sun fara saduwa a kan saitin White Lines, wani wasan kwaikwayo game da lalata a Ibiza - amma lokacin da Laura Haddock da saurayin nata Tom Rhys Harries suka tafi neman gida a makon da ya gabata, sun yanke hoton kwanciyar hankali mai sauƙi daga hedonism na tsibirin.
An hango ma'auratan, wadanda suka buga 'yan'uwa a cikin jerin Netflix, yayin da suke kallon wani gidan gona mai ban mamaki a Oxfordshire, wanda ke kan kasuwa akan fam miliyan 1.2.
Sun isa a Range Rover da Laura, 'yar shekara 34, ke tukawa, suna sanye da gajeren wando da fararen kaya, kuma wani dillalin ƙasa ya tarye su a ciki don ya duba gidan mai ɗakuna biyar.
A cikin White Lines, wanda aka yi fim a kaka ta bara, Laura ta buga Zoe Walker, wacce ta gano mummunan ɓangaren Ibiza yayin da take binciken kisan dan uwanta DJ Axel, wanda Tom mai shekaru 28 ya buga.
Labarin dangantakarsu ya bayyana ne a farkon wannan watan, kasa da shekara guda bayan rushewar auren Laura na shekaru shida da Sam Claflin, wanda ya taka rawa a cikin fina-finai na Hunger Games.
Suna da ɗa mai suna Pip, ɗan shekara huɗu, da kuma 'yarsu Margot, 'yar shekara biyu.
Lokacin da suka sanar da rabuwa a watan Agustan da ya gabata, Claflin, mai shekaru 34, ya rubuta a Instagram: "Ni da Laura mun yanke shawarar rabuwa bisa doka. Za mu ci gaba da tafiya ba tare da komai ba sai soyayya, abota da girmamawa ga juna yayin da muke ci gaba da renon danginmu tare".
Laura da Sam sun fara haduwa a shekarar 2011 a wani gwaji kuma Sam, wanda shi ma ya kasance a cikin Peaky Blinders, ya bayyana aurensu a shekarar 2013 a matsayin "sauƙi ɗaya daga cikin manyan nasarorin da ya samu".
Kafin White Lines, Laura ta bayyana a cikin fim na farko na Inbetweeners da kuma wasan kwaikwayo na BBC na shekarar da ta gabata The Capture, yana wasa da lauya Hannah Roberts.
Tom ya bayyana a cikin Inbetweeners sequel da Sky drama Britannia.
Harin da aka kai wa kafafen yada labarai na Najeriya abin damuwa ne sosai - Majalisar Dinkin Duniya.
Majalisar Dinkin Duniya da Burtaniya sun bayyana karuwar hare-haren da ake kaiwa ofisoshin yada labarai da 'yan jarida a Najeriya a matsayin abin damuwa.
Saboda wannan dalili, Majalisar Dinkin Duniya da gwamnatin Burtaniya sun yi kira ga hukumomi da su daina duk wani matsin lamba da suke yi wa bangaren yada labarai da ma'aikatansa, saboda hakan ya zama dole domin za a tuhumi hukumomin da laifin cin zarafin.
Jakadan Birtaniya a Najeriya, Catriona Laing, ta bayyana hakan ne a ranar Litinin a taron 2020 na ranar hana aikata laifuka a kan 'yan jarida.
Jakadan ya aika sako a shafinsa na Twitter cewa samun cikakken 'yan jarida na da muhimmanci ga kowace gwamnati.
Bai kamata a yi wa 'yan jarida tsangwama ko kuma a kai musu hari ba.
Haka kuma Ronald Kayanja, daraktan sadarwa na Majalisar Dinkin Duniya a Najeriya, ya ce a irin wannan muhimmiyar rana, ya zama dole a bayyana a fili cewa ana kare 'yan jarida da ofisoshin yada labarai.
Kayanja ya ce hare-haren da aka kai wa kafafen yada labarai da ma'aikatan kafofin yada labarai suna da matukar damuwa, kuma saboda wannan ya yi kira ga hukumomi da su binciki zargin irin wannan cin zarafin domin tabbatar da gaskiya da adalci.
Kayanja ya ce wani mataki na kawar da labaran karya shine ta hanyar tallafawa kafofin watsa labarai masu zaman kansu.
Kamar yadda ake tallafawa sauran bangarorin tattalin arziki, domin sake gina su da karfafa su, zai yi kyau a tallafawa kafafen yada labarai. Mun kawo muku rahotanni da suka nuna cewa akwai aƙalla kafafen watsa labarai uku da aka ƙone yayin tarzoma don kawo ƙarshen SARS, tare da 'yan jarida da yawa da suka ji rauni yayin da suke yin aikinsu don gaya wa duniya yadda zanga-zangar ke gudana.
